Job Description:
Roles and Responsibilities:
• Understand Canadian immigration categories and requirements for each category;
• Collect information and documentation from the applicant or client, and ensure that communications are responded to within 24-48 business hours;
• Doing the prescreening of the potential clients against the eligibility criteria for each category and based on the services we offer;
• Make the appropriate revisions to drafts as instructed and obtaining approval from the applicant or client upon finalization;
• Facilitate phone or in-person preparatory or “mock” interviews with the applicant in order to prepare them for immigration interviews;
• Update and maintaining internal Client Management Software systems and databases on a daily basis to ensure that all communication records are available and organized; and
• Respond to clients’ inquiries by phone/ email;
• Schedule meetings, appointments;
• Manage calendar;
• Coordinate requests for documents from clients and client stakeholders and communicating with clients from the start to finish of all immigration processes;
• Prioritize workload and complete tasks under time constraints;
• Conducting research when necessary and ensuring forms and other documents needed for submissions are current;
• Set up and maintain computerized information filing systems;
• Any other duty assigned by the management.

Salary:
12,000,000 VND - 25,000,000 VND

Job Requirements:
• Minimum 1 year of legal administrative experience in an immigration firm;
• Superior communication skills, both verbal and written;
• Strong attention to detail, multi-tasking skills, and organizational skills;
• Knowledge of government portals and online submissions;
• Ability to work on cases independently or with limited supervision;
• Strong interpersonal skills, with the ability to build and maintain healthy client relations as well as employee relations;
• Demonstrated expertise and efficiency with time management, multi-tasking and problem-solving abilities.

Job Description:
